# IIS-DeployApp and DedgeAuth

`DevTools\WebSites\IIS-DeployApp\` deploys apps as IIS virtual applications under Default Web Site.

## Post-Copy Automation

After file copy, `Deploy-IISSite` in `IIS-Handler.psm1` automatically:

1. **Normalizes `DedgeAuth:AuthServerUrl`** in `appsettings.json` to `http://localhost/{path}` (server-agnostic, no hardcoded hostnames)
2. **Patches `web.config`** to set `maxQueryString="8192"` for JWT token redirects

These steps ensure apps work on any server without manual config changes.

## Deploy Templates

- Templates live in `templates\*.deploy.json`
- Naming convention: `<SiteName>_<InstallSource>.deploy.json`
- Key fields: `SiteName`, `PhysicalPath`, `AppType`, `DotNetDll`, `ApiPort`, `HealthEndpoint`

## Key Scripts

| Script | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `IIS-DeployApp.ps1` | Deploy/update a single IIS virtual app from a profile |
| `IIS-RedeployAll.ps1` | Tear down and rebuild ALL IIS apps from templates |
| `IIS-UninstallApp.ps1` | Remove an IIS virtual app and its app pool |
| `Test-IISSite.ps1` | Diagnostics and health checks |

## Consumer App Requirements

Apps using DedgeAuth need these in their `appsettings.json`:

```json
{
  "DedgeAuth": {
    "Enabled": true,
    "AuthServerUrl": "http://localhost/DedgeAuth"
  }
}
```

The deploy system normalizes `AuthServerUrl` automatically, so the published value does not matter.
